Nelson Mandela Bay has recorded 957 new Covid-19 cases. This has taken the metro’s active Covid-19 cases to 2,423 as of Sunday, with Kariega  recording the most  at 263. Despatch and Gelvandale are among the city’s leading hotspots with 196 and 162 cases, respectively. The  metro has recorded 31,648 deaths  and 60,807 recoveries. Health MEC Nomakhosazana Meth announced last week that the Bay was officially in the third wave of Covid-19 infections. The province’s active cases  were 5,623 by Sunday. HeraldLIVE